    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Larry", "content": "Ha. Honest answer? Same." },
    { "type": "narration", "content": "Daniel blinked. Then — slow, like he was deciding whether to allow it — he laughed. Short. Real." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Daniel", "content": "Aight. That's actually funny." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Larry", "content": "I wasn't trying to be." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Daniel", "content": "That's what made it funny." },
    { "type": "narration", "content": "He didn't move out of the way so much as just stop being a wall. A girl nearby who'd caught the whole thing looked at Larry like he'd done something she didn't expect." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Girl", "content": "How'd you do that?" },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Larry", "content": "Do what?" },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Girl", "content": "Nobody makes Daniel laugh. Like ever." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Larry", "content": "I just told the truth." },
    { "type": "dialogue", "speaker": "Girl", "content": "Yeah. That's why." },
    { "type": "consequence", "id": "made_daniel_laugh", "character": "Daniel Snyder", "text": "will remember that." },
    {
      "type": "choice",
      "prompt": "She's still looking at you. What does Larry do?",
      "options": [
